Qualifications:
1. An associate degree in Paralegal Studies, Legal Studies, or a related field and one (1) year of paralegal or legal assistant experience;
2. OR a Certified Paralegal Certification approved by a national association or American Bar Association (ABA) approved program and two (2) years of experience as a paralegal or a legal assistant;
3. OR a high school diploma or equivalent education and three (3) years of experience as a paralegal or legal assistant.
4. Ability to sit and stand for extended periods of time.
5. Exhibit manual dexterity and hand-eye coordination to operate a computer, keyboard, photocopier, telephone, calculator and other office equipment.
